<section class="section py-5">
  <div class="container px-4 px-lg-5">
    <div class="row gx-5">
      <div class="col">
        <div>
          <h2 class="fw-bolder mb-3">And now, some fun facts‚ùó</h2>
          <ul class="fa-ul">
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              Only news items published on the same day are included in
              each episode.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              No personal opinions are expressed in the podcast. The news items are
              presented as they are, without any commentary (Although the LLM may add a reaction, or two!).
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
               Summaries generated using <a href="https://www.wired.co.uk/article/how-chatgpt-works-large-language-model">LLMs</a> may lack full context, nuance, and may inadvertently introduce biases or inaccuracies due to the limitations of the model and the potential for misinterpretation of input. That's why the links to the articles are there for you to go and check for yourself if you need to!
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              The text to speech technology is not perfect. Sometimes, the
              pronunciation of locale-specific words (that is, Zambian words,
              names, places, etc.) is not correct. After some experimenting,
              I found that, of all the English voices available, the one
              with better pronunciation is
              <a
                href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/polly/latest/dg/voicelist.html"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >Ayanda from South Africa</a
              >. I think there's work that needs to be done towards having
              a Zambian English
              <a
                href="https://www.science.co.il/language/Locale-codes.php"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >locale</a
              >, just as we have South African English, Australian
              English, etc. Perhaps you and I can do something about this?
              ü§î
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              Because the news items are presented as summaries, the
              podcast episodes are usually short, between 2 and 10 minutes
              long, depending on the number of news items on that day.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              Links to the original news articles are included in the show
              notes, so you can read the full articles if you want to know
              more.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              This whole thing is an experiment in automation and
              artificial intelligence. The best way to learn a craft is by
              building things, and that's what I'm doing here. I'm
              learning as I go, and I'm having a lot of fun doing it. I
              hope you enjoy listening to the podcast as much as I enjoy
              tinkering with the technology behind it.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="fa-li">
                <i class="text-success fa-solid fa-caret-right"></i>
              </span>
              The idea for this project was actually inspired by
              <a
                href="https://camrobjones.com/hackercast/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >Hackercast</a
              >, an AI-generated podcast summary of
              <a
                href="https://news.ycombinator.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >Hacker News</a
              >.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
